# Commands Reference (v1.0)
Master list of essential commands across major environments.
Each entry includes: command, description, and OS/environment.

---

# 1. Shell Environments

## Bash / Linux / Termux
- ls — list files (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- cd <dir> — change directory (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- pwd — print working directory (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- cp <src> <dst> — copy files (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- mv <src> <dst> — move/rename files (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- rm <file> — delete file (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- rm -r <dir> — delete directory recursively (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- mkdir <dir> — create directory (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- touch <file> — create empty file (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- cat <file> — print file contents (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- nano <file> — edit file (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- chmod +x <file> — make file executable (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- ps aux — list running processes (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- kill <pid> — terminate process (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- top / htop — system monitor (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- curl <url> — HTTP request (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- wget <url> — download file (Linux/Unix/Termux)
- ssh user@host — connect to remote machine (Linux/Unix/Termux)

