# 2. Windows CMD
- dir — list files (Windows)
- cd <dir> — change directory (Windows)
- copy <src> <dst> — copy files (Windows)
- move <src> <dst> — move files (Windows)
- del <file> — delete file (Windows)
- rmdir /s <dir> — delete directory (Windows)
- tasklist — list processes (Windows)
- taskkill /PID <id> /F — kill process (Windows)
- ipconfig — network info (Windows)
- ping <host> — test connectivity (Windows)

---

# 3. PowerShell
- Get-ChildItem — list files (Windows/PowerShell)
- Set-Location — change directory (Windows/PowerShell)
- Copy-Item — copy files (Windows/PowerShell)
- Move-Item — move files (Windows/PowerShell)
- Remove-Item — delete files (Windows/PowerShell)
- Get-Process — list processes (Windows/PowerShell)
- Stop-Process -Id <id> — kill process (Windows/PowerShell)
- Invoke-WebRequest <url> — download file (Windows/PowerShell)

---

# 4. Git
- git init — create repo (All OS)
- git clone <url> — clone repo (All OS)
- git add . — stage changes (All OS)
- git commit -m "msg" — commit changes (All OS)
- git push — upload changes (All OS)
- git pull — download changes (All OS)
- git status — show repo state (All OS)
- git branch — list branches (All OS)
- git checkout <branch> — switch branch (All OS)

---

# 5. Python
- python file.py — run script (All OS)
- pip install <pkg> — install package (All OS)
- pip freeze — list installed packages (All OS)
- python -m venv venv — create virtual env (All OS)
- source venv/bin/activate — activate venv (Linux/Mac/Termux)
- venv\Scripts\activate — activate venv (Windows)

---

# 6. Node / npm
- node file.js — run script (All OS)
- npm init -y — create project (All OS)
- npm install <pkg> — install package (All OS)
- npm run <script> — run script (All OS)

---

# 7. Docker
- docker ps — list containers (All OS)
- docker images — list images (All OS)
- docker run <img> — run container (All OS)
- docker stop <id> — stop container (All OS)
- docker rm <id> — remove container (All OS)
- docker build -t name . — build image (All OS)

---

# 8. Systemctl (Linux servers)
- systemctl start <svc> — start service (Linux)
- systemctl stop <svc> — stop service (Linux)
- systemctl restart <svc> — restart service (Linux)
- systemctl status <svc> — service status (Linux)
- systemctl enable <svc> — auto-start on boot (Linux)

---

# 9. Networking Tools
- ping <host> — test connectivity (All OS)
- traceroute <host> — trace route (Linux/Mac)
- tracert <host> — trace route (Windows)
- ifconfig — network info (Linux/Mac)
- ip addr — network info (Linux)
- netstat -tulpn — open ports (Linux)
- nslookup <domain> — DNS lookup (All OS)
- dig <domain> — DNS lookup (Linux/Mac)

---

# 10. Termux-Specific
- pkg update — update packages
- pkg install <pkg> — install package
- termux-setup-storage — enable storage access
- termux-open <file> — open file with Android app
- termux-wake-lock — prevent sleep
- termux-wake-unlock — allow sleep

---

# 11. SQL (Generic)
- SELECT * FROM table; — read data
- INSERT INTO table (...) VALUES (...); — add data
- UPDATE table SET ... WHERE ...; — modify data
- DELETE FROM table WHERE ...; — remove data
- CREATE TABLE name (...); — create table

---

# 12. Redis
- redis-cli — open shell
- SET key value — set key
- GET key — get key
- DEL key — delete key
- KEYS * — list keys
- FLUSHALL — delete everything (danger)

